The patch overall looks good to me, just a few nits:

{code}
+    if (increaseRequests == null)
+      return;
{code}
{code}
+    if (increasedContainers == null)
+      return;
{code}
Should use curly braces in these places.

{code}
+                throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
+
{code}
Blank line not necessary.

Method annotations should follow similar methods in the same class. I.e. getters should be Public and Stable and setters should be Private and Unstable.

